    "For example, on a large corn farm in the Midwest, integrating IoT soil sensors and weather monitoring systems resulted in a 15% boost in corn yield.",
    "The use of IoT technologies, such as GPS-guided tractors and drone-based imaging, has optimized planting and harvesting schedules, leading to substantial improvements in crop yield (Balafoutis et al. 2017).",
    "Furthermore, IoT applications have greatly enhanced the efficiency of resource utilization, including water, fertilizers, and pesticides.",
    "In California's Central Valley, for instance, IoT-enabled irrigation systems have successfully reduced water usage by 30%, as reported by the University of California, Davis.",
